  "articleSummary": "The article argues that many teams prematurely adopt Algolia for site search without first evaluating whether their content consists of static HTML pages, in which case the author recommends Pagefind as a simpler, build-time alternative. It contrasts Pagefind’s approach—indexing already-deployed HTML and generating static assets—with Algolia’s live, external index, which introduces synchronization complexity and a “second system.” The tone is analytical and tutorial-like, aimed at developers, and uses metaphors such as “infrastructure cosplay” and “the index follows the artifact” to frame the decision. While endorsing Pagefind for content sites like blogs and documentation, it acknowledges where Algolia remains necessary (live writes, permissions, custom ranking).",
